1. Initialize a Node.js Project
First, set up a new Node.js project by creating a project directory and initializing it:

mkdir staticWebsiteServer

cd staticWebsiteServer

npm init -y

2. Install Express
Install express to easily manage routing and serving static files:

npm install express

3. Create the Directory Structure
Your project structure will look like this:

staticWebsiteServer
├── public
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── styles.css
│   └── script.js
├── server.js
└── package.json

4. Create a Static Website
Inside the public folder, add a simple HTML page, along with optional CSS and JavaScript files.

public/practice.html

5. Create the Node.js Server
In the server.js file, create an Express server to serve the static files from the public directory.

server.js

6. Run the Server
Start your server by running:

node server.js

